The formula has a direct operational reading. For each unit of AI deployed, the firm must commit units of defensive expenditure at the interior optimum. This multiplier rises with both breach-loss magnitude and capability : under gap conditions, more capable systems require more defense per unit of deployment to hold breach probability constant. A firm upgrading from to therefore faces a higher per-unit defense burden even before the productivity gain materializes. When , the expected marginal benefit of AI-specific defense falls below its cost, and the firm allocates zero to that margin.
